WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.033 --> 00:00:13.033
 Live cameras on the network will appear as a green light. 

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:22.000
 Here we see the main sections of the web user interface. Registration, operation and administration. 

00:00:23.066 --> 00:00:27.066
 Here are the camera controls (PTZ) used to control the camera's field of view. 

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:37.000
 By clicking and holding down the left mouse button you can change the view of the camera. 

00:00:38.033 --> 00:00:56.000
 You can move the camera horizontally, vertically or diagonally. 

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:34.033
 Click here to have the camera perform a vertical or horizontal patrol. Click pause to stop. 

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:43.066
 Use open / stop alarm if you have connected the alarm to an external system. 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:02:00.066
 The image of the camera may be reversed, depending on the mounting position. 

00:02:01.066 --> 00:02:05.066
 The camera can record up to four positions to patrol automatically when clicked. 

00:02:08.033 --> 00:02:12.033
 Move the camera to a desired position ... 

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.033
 click on "Together" 

00:02:19.066 --> 00:02:23.066
 Move the camera ... 

00:02:26.066 --> 00:02:33.066
 Click "Go" to return to the saved position 1. 

00:02:36.066 --> 00:02:47.000
 The "resolution" selector allows you to change the size of the video display. 

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:53.000
 Choose a refresh rate from the "mode" selection for a flicker-free display. 

00:02:55.033 --> 00:03:07.033
 Adjust the brightness and contrast according to the camera frame. 

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:14.000
 Click "All by default" to reset the controls to their default values. 

